33 /********************************************************************
34 *
35 * Standard register and bit definitions for the Texas Instruments
36 * MSP430 microcontroller.
37 *
38 * This file supports assembler and C development for
39 * CC430x613x devices.
40 *
41 * Texas Instruments, Version 1.9
42 *
43 * Rev. 1.0, First Release
44 * Rev. 1.1, added TLV definitions
45 * Rev. 1.2, added some more DMA Trigger definitions
46 * Rev. 1.3, fixed LCDMEM access
47 * Rev. 1.4, changed RTC_A_VECTOR to RTC_VECTOR
48 * Rev. 1.5, clean up of Flash section
49 * Rev. 1.6, Changed access type of DMAxSZ registers to word only
50 * Rev. 1.7 Changed access type of TimerA/B registers to word only
51 * Rev. 1.8 Removed not available Definitions: RF1AIFIV_RFRXIFG and RF1AIFIV_TFRXIFG
52 * Rev. 1.9 Removed not available Definitions: CRCDIRB and CRCRESR
53 *
54 *
55 ********************************************************************/

71 #ifndef SFR_8BIT
72 /* External references resolved by a device-specific linker command file */
73 #define SFR_8BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned char address
74 #define SFR_16BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned int address
75 //#define SFR_20BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned int address
76 typedef void (* __SFR_FARPTR)();
77 #define SFR_20BIT(address) extern __SFR_FARPTR address
78 #define SFR_32BIT(address) extern volatile unsigned long address
79 
80 #endif

118 /* Low Power Modes coded with Bits 4-7 in SR */

120 #ifdef __ASM_HEADER__ /* Begin #defines for assembler */
121 #define LPM0 (CPUOFF)
122 #define LPM1 (SCG0+CPUOFF)
123 #define LPM2 (SCG1+CPUOFF)
124 #define LPM3 (SCG1+SCG0+CPUOFF)
125 #define LPM4 (SCG1+SCG0+OSCOFF+CPUOFF)
126 /* End #defines for assembler */
127 
128 #else /* Begin #defines for C */
129 #define LPM0_bits (CPUOFF)
130 #define LPM1_bits (SCG0+CPUOFF)
131 #define LPM2_bits (SCG1+CPUOFF)
132 #define LPM3_bits (SCG1+SCG0+CPUOFF)
133 #define LPM4_bits (SCG1+SCG0+OSCOFF+CPUOFF)

138 #define LPM0 __bis_SR_register(LPM0_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 0 */
139 #define LPM0_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM0_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 0 */
140 #define LPM1 __bis_SR_register(LPM1_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 1 */
141 #define LPM1_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM1_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 1 */
142 #define LPM2 __bis_SR_register(LPM2_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 2 */
143 #define LPM2_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM2_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 2 */
144 #define LPM3 __bis_SR_register(LPM3_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 3 */
145 #define LPM3_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM3_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 3 */
146 #define LPM4 __bis_SR_register(LPM4_bits) /* Enter Low Power Mode 4 */
147 #define LPM4_EXIT __bic_SR_register_on_exit(LPM4_bits) /* Exit Low Power Mode 4 */
148 #endif /* End #defines for C */
